== LiveData
  LiveData is a Rails Plugin. This plugim can be used to implement the applications like chat, live process montior, etc.,


== Installation
  Step 1 :-
	./script/plugin install git://github.com/siddick/LiveData.git
  Step 2 :-
	Add the following configuration in the config/environments/development.rb, config/environments/production.rb and config/environments/test.rb
		config.threadsafe!

== Example
	Class MainController < ApplicationController

	  def get_msg
	    user_id = params[:id] || "test"
	    chat = LiveData.get('chat')
	    user = chat.get_user( user_id )
	    render :text => user.read
	  end

	  def send_msg
	    user_id = params[:id] || "test"
	    message = params[:msg] || "Nothing"
	    chat = LiveData.get('chat')
	    user = chat.get_user( user_id )
	    user.write( message )
	    render :text => 'Finesh'
	  end
	end

	== Run Webrick Server
		ruby script/server -b 0.0.0.0 -p 3000
	== Browser
		Open two tabs in the web browser
		First tab :-
			http://localhost:3000/main/get_msg/tester
		Second Tab :-
			http://localhost:3000/main/send_msg/tester?msg=Hello World

